        pros:["Captures interactions between multiple time series simultaneously","Answers 'does X predict Y?' via Granger causality tests","Produces impulse response functions showing how shocks propagate","Standard tool for macroeconomic and financial analysis"],
        cons:["Requires all series to be stationary, which often means differencing","Number of parameters explodes with more variables or lags","Assumes linear relationships between series","Hard to interpret with many variables — results become complex"],
        what:"Multivariate time series model where each variable is regressed on its own lags and all other variables' lags. Captures cross-variable dynamics.",
