        pros:["Discovers subgroups that respond differently to treatment","Uses flexible ML while maintaining causal interpretation","Provides individual-level effect estimates with uncertainty","Enables targeting treatments to those who benefit most"],
        cons:["Requires strong assumptions that all confounders are measured","Needs substantial sample sizes to detect heterogeneity reliably","More complex to implement and interpret than average treatment effects","Can find spurious subgroups if not properly validated"],
        what:"ML approach estimating Conditional Average Treatment Effect (CATE) for each individual or subgroup. Identifies who benefits most from treatment.",
