        pros:["Much faster than MCMC — minutes instead of hours","Scales to large datasets and complex models","Optimization-based: leverages standard deep learning infrastructure","Good enough for many practical applications"],
        cons:["Approximation may miss important features of the true distribution","Tends to underestimate uncertainty — overconfident predictions","Less accurate than MCMC when MCMC is feasible","Harder to diagnose problems than checking MCMC convergence"],
        what:"Approximates the posterior with a simpler distribution by minimizing KL divergence via optimization (ELBO maximization). Much faster than MCMC.",
