        pros:["Gives direct probability statements: 'B has 95% chance of being better'","Expected loss framework supports principled business decisions","Allows valid early stopping without p-value inflation","Naturally incorporates prior knowledge about typical effect sizes"],
        cons:["Requires choosing a prior, which can be controversial","Computationally more involved than simple t-tests","Less familiar to stakeholders used to p-values","Can be misused if priors are chosen to get desired results"],
